.DS_Store
*.pyc
__pycache__/
.env
*.env

# Raw / derived data (user PII: watch history, interactions, subscriptions) --
# excluded from version control by choice, same policy as the parent Hoichoi repo.
# Exceptions below are the minimal set src/pipeline_series_structured.py actually
# reads/writes -- everything else in data/ (experiment sweeps, old versions, other
# user-watch samples) stays excluded. Append more exceptions here as the pipeline's
# data needs grow.
data/*
!data/content_features_500_tagged.csv
!data/structured_linkage_350ep.csv
!data/series_display_names.csv
!data/user_title_watch_sample_2218.csv
!data/content_features_series_rollup_structured.csv
# Full-catalog scale-up (775 titles: 472 movies + 303 series, vs. the 500-title
# sample above) -- read/written by src/pipeline_full_catalog.py.
!data/content_features_full_tagged.csv
!data/structured_linkage_full.csv
!data/content_features_full_catalog_rollup.csv
# Larger/fresher watch sample (4,800 of a 5,000-user pull -- the last ~200
# users are pending a PostHog outage) -- gives the full 775-title catalog
# real evaluation coverage, unlike the 2,218-user sample above where most
# titles are unseen. Used by src/pipeline_full_catalog.py and backend/app.py.
!data/user_title_watch_sample_5000.csv
# Completion-rate data (content_run_length_secs + created_at) for 1,100 of the
# 5,000 users, pulled from PostHog's cms_v_watch_history_with_content -- used
# by recommender.py to drop confirmed-low-completion watches (<60% of runtime)
# from the CF similarity matrix. Partial coverage by design: falls back to the
# unfiltered watch relation for users/titles this sample doesn't cover.
!data/user_watch_completion_sample_1100.csv
_archive/
